{
  "stem": "21786.6",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when we were already in about 10 hours in the train-- so finally, we got out of them, we are going to do something which is [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] a commando camp of the main camp of Sachsenhausen-Oranienburg, Sachsenhausen-- S-A-C-H-S-A-N-H-A-U-S-E-N hyphen capital O-R-I-E-N-B-U-R-G.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This was the oldest-- there is Mauthausen or Buchenwald, is the oldest concentration camp created by Hitler in 1933 for political prisoners.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were one of the side commandos.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the name of the place is Schwarzheide, written S-C-H-W-A-R-Z-H-E-I-D-E, translated, black meadow.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Black meadow sounds odious, using the same word.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At Schwarzheide?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They gave us food, they gave us bread.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they gave us something.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't remember what it was-- but they gave us food on the way.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the soldiers didn't touch us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, we came out on a platform, which was called Ruhland, R-U-H-L-A-N-D, the land of peace.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it really existed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Again, arranged by five.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we were marched by SS men, who simply didn't know how to handle us-- they were from the main camp.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were already seasoned troopers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they marched us into a camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I have got the plan of the camp here.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The barracks-- they were barracks which were built for prisoners, obviously.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they had triple bunks.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But there had been only very limited amount of bunks in each barrack, so that we were divided, let's say, in one of these things were not more that than 100 people or 150 people.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It was not overcrowded.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes-- you know, we had a kind of an Indian signal system.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It wasn't, I mean, a system that you used fire and smoke.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But you used signs in a sign language, which was transferred from one camp to the other.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
